* the supply and distribution of food, water, fuel, power, medical assistance, shelter and other necessities to affected areas;
* the maintenance of the means of transportation by land, air or water and the control of the transport of persons and things;
* the temporary acquisition or control of any property, undertaking or land;
* the evacuation of people in their own interest and/or that of the public to refuges identified in the National Disaster Plan;
* the entering and search of any premises
* the payment of compensation and remuneration to persons affected by government action under special power, and
* any other matters which may apply to a specific disaster event.

